  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technician / Senior Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>SCOPE </strong></p><p>Reporting to the Director of Engineering, the Technician is responsible for inspecting all M&E systems, fire system and kitchen equipment. The incumbent is required to perform shift duties and other duties as may be arranged by the Director of Engineering or designate. He/she will respond to all work requests from Samfex work order system and attend to all other department maintenance request during shift duties</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>OVERALL OBJECTIVES</strong></p><ul><li>To repair and install all electrical works in guestrooms and hotel premises</li><li>To carry out cosmetic items such as painting works, vanishing works, masonry works, carpentry works, carpet and other building works in guestrooms and hotel premises</li><li>To ensure all work requests are properly logged and executed and updated at the end of each shift duties.</li><li>To assist and supervise all works carried out by outsourced parties</li><li>To ensure all M&E plant keys are kept properly and readily accessible.</li><li>To carry out plumbing and electrical works in and around guestrooms and hotel premise</li><li>Other ad-hoc duties</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Positive, friendly, professional and confident, with good interpersonal skills.</li><li>Possesses a Trade Certificate in Building / Electrical / Mechanical</li><li>Minimum 2 years hotel engineering experiences</li><li>Possesses good knowledge of building equipment: heating, ventilation, plumbing, electricity, automatic operation with experience in the maintenance of buildings and facilities HVACR</li><li>Able to perform shift work.</li></ul>",
